In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims September 13, 2015, as National Grandparents Day in the United States. He highlights the important role that grandparents play in society, emphasizing their love, support, and wisdom. The President acknowledges the sacrifices that grandparents have made throughout their lives and the impact they have had on shaping the country. He praises their determination in overcoming challenges and creating a better future for their families and the nation. President Obama encourages Americans to honor their own grandparents and those in their community on this special day.